.IX Title "XML::Grove::AsCanonXML 3"
.TH XML::Grove::AsCanonXML 3 "perl v5.6.1" "1998-09-25" "User Contributed Perl Documentation"
.UC
.SH "NAME"
\&\s-1XML:\s0:Grove::AsCanonXML \- output \s-1XML\s0 objects in canonical \s-1XML\s0
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\& use XML::Grove::AsCanonXML;
.Ve
.Vb 1
\& $string = $xml_object->as_canon_xml OPTIONS;
.Ve
.Vb 1
\& $writer = new XML::Grove::AsCanonXML OPTIONS;
.Ve
.Vb 2
\& # OPTIONS
\& $writer->comments([$bool]);
.Ve
.Vb 2
\& $string = $writer->as_canon_xml($xml_object);
\& $writer->as_canon_xml($xml_object, $file_handle);
.Ve
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
\&\f(CW\*(C`XML::Grove::AsCanonXML\*(C'\fR will return a string or write a stream of
canonical \s-1XML\s0 for an \s-1XML\s0 object and it's content (if any).
.PP
\&\f(CW\*(C`XML::Grove::AsCanonXML\*(C'\fR objects hold the options used for writing
the \s-1XML\s0 objects.  Options can be supplied when the the object is
created,
.PP
.Vb 1
\&    $writer = new XML::Grove::AsCanonXML comments => 1;
.Ve
or modified at any time before writing an \s-1XML\s0 object using the methods
defined below.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.IX Header "OPTIONS"
.Ip "$writer->comments( [$bool] )" 4
.IX Item "$writer->comments( [$bool] )"
By default comments are not written to the output.  Setting comment to
\&\s-1TRUE\s0 will include comments in the output.
